cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IT

This paper discusses the use of deep learning with Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) for time series prediction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the development and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. The paper also discusses the use of LSTM, which is a specific type of neural network, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the application of these techniques to telecommunication networks, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, since the paper discusses the development of a new model (Random Connectivity LSTM), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category.
